---
// SEC-002 fix: this Astro page used to server-render the last 30 git
// commits, the suburb / insight slug list, the internal API base URL, the
// company UUID, and a GitHub repo URL. All of that was sent to the browser
// before a JS-only password gate ran, so anyone could `curl /dashboard` to
// read it. The fix is to ship nothing sensitive at all from this file.
//
// The real dashboard is the Next.js app at /dashboard/ in this repo, which
// is deployed separately and gated server-side.
---

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <meta name="robots" content="noindex, nofollow" />
    <title>Private</title>
    <style>
      body{margin:0;background:#0f0d0c;color:#f2efe9;font-family:system-ui,-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',sans-serif;min-height:100vh;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;padding:2rem;}
      .card{max-width:420px;text-align:center;}
      .eyebrow{font-size:0.65rem;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:0.18em;text-transform:uppercase;color:#c4912a;margin:0 0 0.75rem;}
      h1{font-family:Georgia,'Times New Roman',serif;font-weight:300;font-size:1.5rem;margin:0 0 1rem;color:#f2efe9;}
      p{font-size:0.9rem;line-height:1.6;color:rgba(242,239,233,0.6);margin:0 0 0.75rem;}
      a{color:#c4912a;text-decoration:none;}
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="card">
      <p class="eyebrow">Daniel Gierach Property</p>
      <h1>Private page</h1>
      <p>This area is not publicly accessible.</p>
      <p><a href="/">Return to danielgierach.com</a></p>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
